Northgate Exploration Ltd saidhourly-paid workers at its two Chibougamau, Quebec mines votedon the weekend to accept a new three-year contract offer andreturned to work today after a one-month strike.    It said the workers, represented by United Steelworkers ofAmerica, would receive a 1.21 dlr an hour pay raise over thelife of the new contract and improved benefits.    Northgate, which produced 23,400 ounces of gold in firstquarter, said that while the strike slowed production, "We arestill looking forward to a very satisfactory performance."    The Chibougamau mines produced 81,500 ounces of gold lastyear. Reuter&#3;